==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sozzle
<hw>Soz"zle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Freq. from
<ets>soss</ets>, v.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To splash or wet carelessly;
<as>as, to <ex>sozzle</ex> the feet in water</as>.</def> <mark>[Local,
U.S.]</mark> <rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To heap up in confusion.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Forby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sozzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sozzle
<hw>Soz"zle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who spills water or
other liquids carelessly; specifically, a sluttish woman.</def>
<mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mass, or heap, confusedly mingled.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spa</ent>⟦br⟧
